<item>
            <title>[FLINK-15838] Dangling CountDownLatch.await(timeout)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-15838</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are 16 occurrences in the codebase (all in test code) when the result of CountDownLatch.await(timeout, TimeUnit) is not checked. It&apos;s like not checking the result of File.delete(). The common fix is to wrap CDL.await() call into assertTrue().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All 16 places could be found using the following structural search in IntelliJ:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$x$.await($y$, $z$);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With &quot;CountDownLatch&quot; type constraint on the $x$ variable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
